
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dget` baraye gereftan (download) package-haye Debian az repository-haye Debian estefade mishavad. In dastoor package-ha ra az manabe online download mikonad, vali anha ra نصب (install) nemikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `dget -d` --> 📦 Faghat download kon, nasb nakon.
    🔹 `dget -u` --> ⬆️ Update kardan list package-ha az repository ghabl az download.
    🔹 `dget -x` --> 📂 Extract kardan source code package bad az download (agar dastras bashad).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dget package_name.dsc

    🔹 Download package ba name `package_name.dsc` az default repository.

    $ dget -d package_name.dsc

    🔹 Faghat package ra download kon, va an ra extract ya install nakon.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dget -x package_name.dsc

    🔹 Package ra download mikonad va source code an ra extract mikonad agar dastras bashad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dget` command is used to download Debian packages from Debian repositories. It downloads packages from online sources, but does not install them.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dget -d` --> 📦 Only download the package, do not install it.
    🔹 `dget -u` --> ⬆️ Update the package list from the repository before downloading.
    🔹 `dget -x` --> 📂 Extract the source code of the package after downloading (if available).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dget package_name.dsc

    🔹 Download the package with the name `package_name.dsc` from the default repository.

    $ dget -d package_name.dsc

    🔹 Only download the package, and do not extract or install it.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dget -x package_name.dsc

    🔹 Downloads the package and extracts its source code if available.
